The Meadowlands race track reported today that thoroughbred racing in 1982 set records in attendance and wagering.

The attendance total of 1.5 million was almost 132,000 more than in 1981. The mutuel handle of $204.3 million was almost $11.7 million higher, and daily crowds averaged 15,321, an increase from 14,699 in 1981.

Herb McCauley took the riding title by winning 100 races, a track record, and earning more than $1.1 million, also a track record.